    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl>Morelli in <ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>221</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>103100</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="divine" ref="#_os"><name nymRef="#_ος"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><seg part="F">ω</seg></name></persName> 
                    <g type="punct">:</g> <persName type="divine" ref="#Hekate"><name nymRef="#Ἑκάτα">Ἑκάτ<supplied reason="lost">ας</supplied></name></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="1"><lem><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ω</lem>
                <rdg resp="#SECir"><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">Κωρήτ</supplied>ω</rdg>
                </app></p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Autels de</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>os et d'Hécate.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altars of</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>os and of Hekate.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Altari di</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>os e di Ecate.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The name of the first deity is not easy to guess; <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἱατρῶ</foreign> or <foreign xml:lang="grc">Πυθίω</foreign> would fit, but it is too
                    hazardous to restore them with only the final letter, inasmuch that there is no other instance of any of them on such altars. Nevertheless, the restoration 
                    tentatively suggested by Morelli is grammatically impossible.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
